# wealth-web tab panels

## One visible main panel per bottom tab

Render tab content **only** when that tab is active (`bottomTab === "ai"` → AI, etc.).

Do **not** mount AI (or any tab) on every route and try to hide it.

## Never use `hidden` on `.portfolio-chat`

`.portfolio-chat` sets `display: flex` in CSS, which overrides the HTML `hidden` attribute. The AI panel will stay visible on every tab.

```css
/* ❌ BAD — hidden attribute is ignored */
.portfolio-chat { display: flex; }

/* ✅ GOOD — if you must keep mounted, use a modifier class */
.portfolio-chat--inactive { display: none !important; }
```

Prefer **conditional render** or **lift state to App** (see `useMunshiChat`) instead of always-mounted hidden panels.

## Persisting AI state across tab switches

- Lift API key + chat session state to `App.tsx` via `useMunshiChat` (survives `PortfolioChatTab` unmount).
- Also persist to `deviceStorage` / `chatHistory` for page refresh.
- Munshi Ji uses **tool calling** — see `server/munshi-tools.md` and `server/munshiToolSchemas.mjs`. Do not dump full portfolio context on every turn.
- Do not equate “persist” with “always mount the AI UI”.

## Before shipping tab or AI changes

1. Click **Home**, **Screener**, **AI**, **Profile** — each must show only its own content.
2. Chat + API key survive switching away from AI and back.
3. Hard refresh — chat history and key restore from storage.
